This paper deals with uncertainty estimation techniques in deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of approximate Bayesian inference methods, which is a common topic in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) subcategory. The paper also deals with robotics applications, which falls under the cs.RO (Robotics) subcategory. The use of uncertainty estimation techniques in image-based reinforcement learning tasks also suggests a connection to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) subcategory. Finally, the paper discusses the use of uncertainty estimation in value-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of control theory, suggesting a connection to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) subcategory.
